<subSubSection id="66F66BC8FFD96622D3E7FCCCFDF472DF" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="136" pageId="1" pageNumber="134" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="2E533843FFD96620D3E7FCCCFCD67025" blockId="1.[674,1212,850,1699]" box="[677,774,850,876]" pageId="1" pageNumber="134">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2E533843FFD96622D3E7FCEFFDF472DF" blockId="1.[674,1212,850,1699]" lastBlockId="3.[111,647,216,401]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="136" pageId="1" pageNumber="134">
The 
<typeStatus id="F15786E1FFD96620D391FCEFFCE570C5" box="[723,821,881,907]" pageId="1" pageNumber="134">lectotype</typeStatus>
shows two large flowering stems and a single sterile stem. The flowering stems are either not widened at the tip or only slightly widened.The widening observed on one of the stems appears to result from dessication or flattening of this stem. The leaves of the flowering stems are narrowly spatulate. As in the population that lives at high altitude, all the leaves of the sterile stems of the type are broadly spatulate. The capitula are very poorly preserved and the bracts were damaged during dissection by botanists. It is thus impossible to know how many external bracts were originally present. The morphological characteristics listed in 
<tableCitation id="636E0DF8FFD96620D529FB73FB697649" box="[1131,1209,1261,1287]" captionStart="TABLE" captionStartId="15.[113,124,219,236]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="TABLE 2. — Summary of the qualitative characteristics of the individuals of Santolina oblongifolia Boiss. that live above and below 1800 m in the Central System of the Iberian Peninsula. Abbreviation: N, number of individuals studied." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/7A9368CBFFD7662ED133FF45FC14724D" pageId="1" pageNumber="134" tableUuid="7A9368CBFFD7662ED133FF45FC14724D">Table 2</tableCitation>
are essential to determine hybrid characters in 
<taxonomicName id="E9EC43C0FFD96620D5CAFA93FD317609" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Santolina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="134" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1C98E451FFD96620D5CAFA93FD317609" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="134">Santolina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’s populations, however the poorly preserved capitula did not allow a complete examination of Boissier’s original material. Therefore, it is not possible to determine if the 
<typeStatus id="F15786E1FFD96620D2E7FA12FBD776E8" box="[933,1031,1420,1446]" pageId="1" pageNumber="134">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="E9EC43C0FFD96620D565FA12FB6976E8" box="[1063,1209,1420,1446]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Santolina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="134" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oblongifolia">
<emphasis id="1C98E451FFD96620D565FA12FB6976E8" box="[1063,1209,1420,1446]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="134">S. oblongifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has hybrid characteristics or not. However, the morphological characteristics of this sample in the G-BOISS herbarium suggests that it was probably collected at an altitude below 
<quantity id="E91495A6FFD96620D2ABF994FBEF756B" box="[1001,1087,1546,1573]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" pageId="1" pageNumber="134" unit="m" value="1800.0">1800 m</quantity>
in a mixed population including 
<taxonomicName id="E9EC43C0FFD96620D2CBF9B4FBC7750A" box="[905,1047,1578,1604]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Santolina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="134" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oblongifolia">
<emphasis id="1C98E451FFD96620D2CBF9B4FBC7750A" box="[905,1047,1578,1604]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="134">S. oblongifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="E9EC43C0FFD96620D561F9B4FC4D752A" authority="subsp. rosmarinifolia" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Santolina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="134" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="rosmarinifolia" subSpecies="rosmarinifolia">
<emphasis id="1C98E451FFD96620D561F9B4FBE0750A" box="[1059,1072,1578,1604]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="134">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="1C98E451FFD96620D57EF9B4FD10752A" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="134">rosmarinifolia</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis id="1C98E451FFD96620D24EF9D4FC4D752A" box="[780,925,1610,1636]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="134">rosmarinifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and their putative hybrids. 
<bibRefCitation id="4A7D45B2FFD96620D3E1F9F7FCA175CA" author="Rivas Goday" box="[675,881,1641,1668]" firstAuthor="Rivas Goday" pageId="1" pageNumber="134" pagination="23 - 30" refId="ref9764" refString="RIVAS GODAY S. 1955. - Ruiz y Pavon discipulos destacados por Gomez Ortega. Anales de la Real Academia de Farmacia 21: 23 - 30." type="journal article" year="1955">Rivas Goday (1955)</bibRefCitation>
considered that probably Pavon collected the original material of 
<taxonomicName id="E9EC43C0FFD96620D544F917FB4D75ED" box="[1030,1181,1673,1699]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Santolina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="134" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oblongifolia">
<emphasis id="1C98E451FFD96620D544F917FB4D75ED" box="[1030,1181,1673,1699]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="134">S. oblongifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in locations close to Casatejada (Cáceres). Casatejada is located south of Central System, at not more than 
<quantity id="E91495A6FFDB6622D12DFE89FF69727C" box="[111,185,279,306]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="136" unit="m" value="300.0">300 m</quantity>
, outside the altitudinal range of this taxon. The present evaluation of the original material of 
<taxonomicName id="E9EC43C0FFDB6622D133FEC9FED5723E" box="[113,261,342,369]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Santolina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="136" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oblongifolia">
<emphasis id="1C98E451FFDB6622D133FEC9FED5723E" box="[113,261,342,369]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="136">S. oblongifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
suggests that the 
<typeStatus id="F15786E1FFDB6622D081FEC8FDF5723E" box="[451,549,342,368]" pageId="3" pageNumber="136">lectotype</typeStatus>
does not match with the current use of the name.
</paragraph>
